title: ICE during borrow check HRTB & Self type

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=03575f5ac3e8419c0bd8efb8bd1846f5 ```rs use std::marker::PhantomData; pub struct NfaBuilder<'brand> { brand: PhantomData<&'brand mut &'brand mut ()>, } impl NfaBuilder<'_> { pub fn with) -> R>(f: F) -> R { Brand::with(|brand| { // This should be using NfaBuilder instead of Self becuase they have diffrent lifetime constraints f(Self { brand: brand.lt, }) }) } } #[derive(Clone, Copy)] pub struct Brand<'brand> { lt: PhantomData<&'brand mut &'brand mut ()>, } impl Brand<'_> { pub fn with) -> R>(f: F) -> R { f(Self { lt: PhantomData }) } } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` binary: rustc commit-hash: a55dd71d5fb0ec5a6a3a9e8c27b2127ba491ce52 commit-date: 2022-09-19 host: aarch64-apple-darwin release: 1.64.0 LLVM version: 14.0.6 ``` ### Error output ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'called `Option::unwrap()` on a `None` value', compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/diagnostics/region_errors.rs:691:70 ```
